{"questionId":"22643153","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Diego is a teacher in the school. He believes that the number of students, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>, who have had influenza during the first&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> days of the school year, can be modelled by the function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>250</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>240</mn><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Using this model, calculate how many days it will take for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn></math> students to have had influenza since the start of the school year.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>250</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>240</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>22</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>22</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6303</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>23</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></strong>(days)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22643153","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.1f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Using this model, calculate how many days it will take for 200 students to have had influenza since the start o